{"id":"4oHnAeYNUYIa5Ia4","meta":{"instanceId":"8aef42074eff4988bb0167a37c08b561db4946dc354bdb23e637dbf612048834"},"name":"Pdf Generator","tags":[],"nodes":[{"id":"8b404fdf-0a7f-4ead-b970-0941b4054464","name":"Sticky Note","type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","position":[-192,-160],"parameters":{"width":480,"height":784,"content":"## Pdf Generator\n\n### How it works\n\nThis workflow generates PDF-style output from form submissions using Google Drive and Google Docs. It receives an uploaded file through a form, extracts items from it, loops through each item, creates a document copy, updates the document content, downloads the result, and uploads the finished file back to Drive. The upload step feeds back into the loop so multiple extracted items can be processed one by one.\n\n### Setup steps\n\n- Configure the form trigger with the required upload field and any fields needed to populate the document.\n- Set up credentials for Google Drive and Google Docs nodes.\n- Configure the copy step with the correct template or source file ID and destination folder.\n- Map extracted fields into the Google Docs update step so placeholders are replaced correctly.\n- Configure the download and upload Google Drive nodes with the desired export format and output folder.\n\n### Customization\n\nAdjust the loop batch size, document template, placeholder mappings, export format, and destination folder to match the desired PDF generation process."},"typeVersion":1},{"id":"57144f51-b1b3-40ff-b20f-07c1a96aa436","name":"Sticky Note1","type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","position":[368,-128],"parameters":{"color":7,"width":608,"height":304,"content":"## Receive and batch input\n\nStarts when a form is submitted, extracts uploaded file data, and prepares the extracted items for batch processing through the loop."},"typeVersion":1},{"id":"bfb03424-9306-4e92-905f-02411cd22fdc","name":"Sticky Note2","type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","position":[1104,-144],"parameters":{"color":7,"width":400,"hei